-- Bombardier, Silvercorp, Silver Wheaton: Canadian Equity Preview
-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 2010-11-26T14:04:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/bombardier-silvercorp-silver-wheaton-canadian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Canadian trading.   Bombardier Inc.  (BBD/B CT): The third-largest maker of
civic aircraft’s C-series jetliner, which has won orders from
only three customers, is a leading contender for a contract from
SAS Group as the biggest Nordic airline prepares to add as many
as 55 planes over six years.  SAS, already one of Bombardier’s biggest European clients,
is evaluating the CS300 variant of the CSeries, seating 120 to
145 people, Niklas Hardange, the carrier’s fleet-planning chief,
said in an interview at its headquarters in Stockholm.  Silvercorp Metals Inc.  (SVM CT): The Vancouver-based mining
company with operations in China was cut to “market perform”
from “outperform” by  Andrew Kaip , an analyst at Bank of
Montreal.  Silver Wheaton Corp.  (SLW CT): The Vancouver-based
purchaser and seller of the metal was raised to “outperform”
from “market perform” by  David Haughton , equity analyst at
Bank of Montreal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang at   ihwang7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
